🧾 Terraform Configuration
🔹 CloudWatch CPU Alarm
provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

resource "aws_cloudwatch_metric_alarm" "cpu_alarm" {
  alarm_name          = "datacenter-alarm"
  comparison_operator = "GreaterThanThreshold"
  evaluation_periods  = 1
  metric_name         = "CPUUtilization"
  namespace           = "AWS/EC2"
  period              = 300
  statistic           = "Average"
  threshold           = 80

  dimensions = {
    InstanceId = "i-1234567890abcdef0"
  }
}
🔍 Key Concepts Applied
1. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)

We defined monitoring infrastructure using Terraform, making it:

Repeatable
Version-controlled
Automatable
2. Cloud Monitoring with CloudWatch

CloudWatch continuously collects metrics such as:

CPU utilization
Network activity
Disk I/O

We configured an alarm based on CPU usage thresholds.

3. Threshold-Based Alerting

Alarm logic:

IF CPUUtilization > 80%
FOR 5 minutes
THEN trigger ALARM state
4. Time-Based Evaluation
Period: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
Evaluation periods: 1

This means a single breach triggers the alarm.

